document.title: 2023 Indiana Academic Standards: Kindergarten - Grade 5 Physical Education

1C4BB64056C14ACAA6B577E84B9BDC1F.description:
Describes the social benefits gained from participating in physical activity
(such as recess, youth sport).

609AD18C36224A5D9061DE3131E8EF4D.description:
Analyzes different physical activities for enjoyment and challenge,
identifying reasons for a positive or negative response.

693615A0D25A46848F1588C2D2D46B40.description:
Expresses (such as written essay, visual art, creative dance) the
enjoyment and/or challenge of participating in a favorite physical activity.

B0FB7F492C664372BB1D605DDEC0576C.description:
Compares the health benefits of participating in selected physical
activities.

124E26DC04FF4B9E92E8A5E1A105D780.description: Valuing Health, Enjoyment, Challenge, Self Expression, and Social Interaction

816A4EF8896A46C3BA9F51E381990B66.description:
The physically literate individual recognizes the value of physical activity for health,
enjoyment, challenge, self expression and/or social interaction.

F2D5B14401D042A78EDE4E43A491CC90.description:
Works safely with peers, independently, and with/without equipment in
physical activity settings.

B62A79B86BFA40859B4D63909E41D51C.description: Critiques the etiquette involved in rules of various game activities.

66F133F396784B85A3734176741F0BAA.description:
Accepts, recognizes and actively involves others with both higher and lower
skill abilities into physical activities and group projects.

87C50566B1B643209014D2C92DF0F45B.description: Gives corrective feedback respectfully to peers.

1EF3DDB7A08F4B7D890EA5D928620DC1.description:
Exhibits respect for self with appropriate behavior while engaging in physical
activity.

E36FE1FD342349A99BBEF771CD3D0716.description:
Participates with responsible personal behavior in a variety of physical activity
contexts, environments and facilities.

7C4698A25E98403D92EACFFC4FEA318B.description:
Engages in physical activity with responsible interpersonal behavior (such as
peer to peer, student to teacher, student to referee).

8BB3C0F4D6624DF29528FC94EC051B56.description:
The physically literate individual exhibits responsible personal and social behavior
that respects self and others.

FCD2D5E299BB4AFF80FB21D5534D2F11.description:
Analyzes the impact of food choices relative to physical activity, youth sports
and personal health.

A76D507ADBE341BFB5E6142EBEFFDF99.description: Describes connections between body systems and their role in movement.

99E339DB794947DCA50B77A5DADCC4D0.description:
Designs a fitness plan to address ways to use physical activity to enhance
fitness.

E503683F86094769A90B1D970118319C.description:
Analyzes results of fitness assessment (pre and post), comparing results to
fitness components for good health.

B1DF980F03D14778B63B82DBE20AB248.description:
Identifies the need for warm-up and cool-down relative to various physical
activities.

5DD35E65BB684B9CBD5BA80E83C5D67A.description: Differentiates between skill-related and health-related fitness.

3D8146B53F08488A8A8284CD33019C81.description:
Actively engages in the activities of physical education class, both teacher
directed and independent.

861578C565B1453D92BEA9FF5440C3AD.description:
Documents and analyzes physical activity outside physical education class for
fitness benefits of activities.

5645EA8866E04BAFBC28671C6E3DCEEF.description:
The physically literate individual demonstrates the knowledge and skills to achieve
and maintain a health-enhancing level of physical activity and fitness.

E8FE6F57397E4E1197059EA7A0AEDBAC.description:
Recognizes the type of throw, volley or striking action needed for different games
and sports situations.

33B7A3A34E6146A0816F61DAE52602B9.description: Applies basic offensive and defensive strategies and tactics in net/wall small-sided practice tasks.

B40C4EED6F9D474D8B6A735C1A7AD323.description:
Applies basic offensive and defensive strategies/ tactics in invasion small-sided
practice tasks.

977B9184ADB94B71816857772789BCB3.description:
Analyzes movement situations and applies movement concepts (such as force,
direction, speed, pathways, extensions) in small-sided practice tasks in game
environments, dance or gymnastics.

CE03D2462662498F99E9DD2E49EE0BBC.description: Applies the concepts of direction and force to strike an object with an implement.

F665D90D25AC4C13AB0882CB915D1449.description: Applies movement concepts to strategy in game situations.

CDE97CE6ECAA42128AC7E4C0B0CB018C.description:
Combines movement concepts with skills in small-sided practice tasks (such as
in game environments, gymnastics and dance with self-direction).

441498BBB825470B8AB4469ED6EC305F.description:
Combines spatial concepts with locomotor and nonlocomotor movements for
small groups (such as in gymnastics, dance and game environments).

80B86DF6CCA74503A9B9E5781CE31E14.description:
The physically literate individual applies knowledge of concepts, principles,
strategies and tactics related to movement and performance.

A4CA88776CC7442089D446E6702562DD.description:
Creates a jump-rope routine with a partner (such as jumping in a figure 8, front to
back, etc., and with short rope, long rope, double dutch, jump bands).

461456A6AC0547B6972CA0A332703A78.description:
Combines striking with a long implement (such as a bat, hockey stick) with
receiving and traveling skills in a small-sided game.

C2422E9EF8C34E8BB58A5EA0D58D4BF4.description: Strikes a pitched ball with a bat using a mature pattern.

892AF0F9F18F4AB8A188D82653AFD3A9.description: Strikes an object consecutively, with a partner, using a short-handed implement,

8C705E6FA09845C08A66DE90693D7078.description:
Applies mature patterns while striking an object underhand in a variety of activities
(such as modified games, and small-sided game play).

D3F08EB220DC445AAC01B8232525B9CA.description:
Applies mature patterns while receiving with the foot in a variety of activities (such
as 1v1 practice tasks, modified games, and small-sided game play).

5A510861490E49D68691A3B28840DD78.description:
Combines foot dribbling with other skills (such as 1v1 practice tasks, modified
games, and small-sided game play).

05EAB9152A2E4CC49BAA82B727E3CF17.description:
Demonstrates mature patterns in kicking and punting in small-sided practice task
environments.

C59F238CA4E242369B4144B7517D94BA.description:
Passes and receives a pass with the feet using a mature pattern as both partners
travel.

1C987E951EE04832848C10618B06E009.description: Combines hand dribbling with other skills during 1v1 practice tasks.

206F577D0BA84D8ABFFE1910F715B76B.description: Catches with reasonable accuracy in dynamic, small-sided practice tasks.

5B2BEEA21ED443D8A5410E73359EF822.description:
Catches a ball above the head, at chest or waist level, and along the ground using
a mature pattern in a non-dynamic environment.

759729A963574DDB93BFCC39387641BC.description: Passes with reasonable accuracy in dynamic, small- sided practice tasks.

DB51CFBF53DC4724970D9A495E3831C7.description: Passes with accuracy, both partners moving.

86CC06CC9CFB496FAEF64100671EF20E.description:
Performs mature pattern in an overhand throw in a variety of activities, modified
games, and small-sided games.

C91E3C28C4FC4766B161D8F54F348E8C.description: Performs mature pattern in an overhand throw to a moving partner.

7E47114014DC4E5EAFCEE22DD44371B4.description: Performs mature pattern in an overhand throw at varying distances.

FD7F01B192F942F485B140AA5953CFCC.description:
Applies mature pattern in an underhand throw in a variety of activities, modified
games, and small-sided game play.

C83033371D1040EF9E2F86A47D330A8E.description:
Transfers weight in various activities (such as gymnastics, dance environments,
striking, throwing).

D59935055ECB4853B5EB42D798C475D8.description:
Combines balance and transferring weight (such as in a gymnastics sequence,
yoga, dance with a partner).

47AC4C2E6F484615A1C7BBFD57420662.description:
Applies mature patterns in nonlocomotor skills in a variety of activities, modified
games, and small-sided game play.

F6C197878BC9467CBA0D243B5F7E3333.description:
Creates and demonstrates a routine using complex rhythmic combinations (such as
self-dance, Jump Bands, group dance) with correct rhythm and pattern.

1B9C256CA69A420786CFA7C5C3FF141C.description:
Combines jumping and landing patterns with locomotor and manipulative skills
(such as in dance, educational gymnastics and small-sided practice tasks and game
environments).

0FBC9DC3CC524FCCA1F4BD671A652CB0.description: Locomotor (Jumping and landing in a horizontal and vertical plane)

03EF7B2D04A5435996B535020DD8A34A.description: Applies appropriate pacing in a variety of running distances.

517814E4BB04416BAD9588E1DB14A5C5.description:
Applies mature patterns in locomotor skills in a variety of activities, modified games,
and small-sided game play.

CB293A7EEF1E47C8A43C24C337FDC6EC.description: Locomotor (Hopping, galloping, running, sliding, skipping, leaping, walking, running)

209AA456768043E1B9EA6A0D1BF59583.description:
The physically literate individual will demonstrate competency in a variety of motor
skills and movement patterns.
